    "what_description": "Octomeria nemorosa is a species of orchid that belongs to the family Orchidaceae. It is an epiphytic orchid, with a caespitose habit, producing one to several stems, each carrying a single flower. The flowers are yellowish-green to greenish-yellow in color, with a lip that is three-lobed and a column that is three-forked, containing a pollinium. The plant has leaves that are lanceolate to elliptic in shape, measuring up to 10 cm in length, and are arranged in two rows along the stem. The species is native to South America, specifically in the tropical regions of Brazil, Argentina, and Paraguay.",
