    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Octomeria nemorosa are infusion, tea, tincture, salve, and decoction. Infusion is prepared by steeping dried flowers in hot water to make a tea that is used to treat various health issues, including fever, cough, and respiratory problems. Decoction is prepared by boiling the roots in water for a longer period to make a strong tea that is used to treat digestive issues, such as diarrhea and constipation. Tincture is prepared by steeping the dried flowers in a solvent like ethanol to make a concentrated liquid that is used to treat fever, headache, and other health issues. A salve is prepared by infusing the roots in a carrier oil to make a topical treatment that is used to soothe skin irritations and wounds.",
